{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M8hYjhcTo6x7NYVENZSdEY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and documented the complete architecture for web UI structure, container deletion functionality, run management, and related infrastructure. Here are the findings:\n\n### 1. WEB UI STRUCTURE\n\n**HTML Templates** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`):\n- `layout.html` - Base layout template with navbar and content block\n- `projects.html` - Project overview/landing page with health dots and project cards\n- `runs.html` - Runs list page with filtering by project\n- `run_detail.html` - Individual run details with steps, logs, and container controls\n- `project_detail.html` - Dedicated project page with panels for info, workflows, and container management\n\n**HTTP Routes** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 146-164):\n```\nGET  /                              handleProjectOverview\nGET  /projects/{name}/runs          handleProjectRuns\nGET  /runs                           handleRunsList\nGET  /runs/{id}                      handleRunDetail\nGET  /projects/{name}                handleProjectDetail (NEW)\nGET  /api/projects                   handleAPIProjects\nGET  /api/runs                       handleAPIRuns\nGET  /api/runs/{id}                  handleAPIRunDetail\nGET  /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\nPOST /api/runs/{id}/stop             handleAPIStopRun\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container      handleAPIDeleteContainer\nDELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers\nGET  /api/projects/{name}/info       handleAPIProjectInfo\nPOST /api/runs/{id}/stream           handleAPIStream (SSE)\nGET  /static/*                       Static files\n```\n\n**Handler Interfaces** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 61-88):\n- `ContainerLogger` - Logs retrieval interface\n- `ContainerManager` - Extends ContainerLogger with Stop, Remove, Inspect methods\n- `TaskProvider` - Task pipeline state retrieval\n\n### 2. CONTAINER DELETION FUNCTIONALITY\n\n**gRPC Service Definition** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`):\n```protobuf\nrpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse);\n\nmessage DeleteContainerRequest {\n  string id = 1;  // Can be run ID or container ID\n}\nmessage DeleteContainerResponse {}\n```\n\n**Delete Implementation - Single Container** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 719-755):\n```go\nhandleAPIDeleteContainer(w, r)\n- Accepts run ID in URL path\n- Gets run from store\n- Calls mgr.Remove(containerID)\n- Sets ContainerKept = false\n- Returns {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n```\n\n**Delete Implementation - Project Containers** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 757-816):\n```go\nhandleAPIDeleteProjectContainers(w, r)\n- Lists all runs for a project\n- Iterates through runs where ContainerKept == true\n- Skips running containers (via mgr.Inspect)\n- Removes stopped containers\n- Updates run.ContainerKept = false\n- Returns {\"deleted\": N, \"errors\": [...]}\n```\n\n**CLI Command** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` lines 425-437):\n```bash\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n- Calls client.DeleteContainer(ctx, &pb.DeleteContainerRequest{Id: args[0]})\n```\n\n**gRPC Server Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 698-731):\n```go\nDeleteContainer(ctx, req)\n- Resolves ID as run ID first\n- Falls back to treating as container ID directly\n- Calls s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID)\n- Clears ContainerKept flag\n- Returns DeleteContainerResponse\n```\n\n### 3. RUN STORE INTERFACE AND MANAGEMENT\n\n**RunStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n```go\nCreateRun(ctx, run) error\nGetRun(ctx, id) (*Run, error)\nUpdateRun(ctx, run) error\nDeleteRun(ctx, id) error\nListRuns(ctx, since) ([]*Run, error)\nListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, since) ([]*Run, error)\nListProjects(ctx) ([]string, error)\nListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID) ([]*Run, error)\n```\n\n**SQLite Store Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`):\n- `GetRun()` - Queries single run by ID (line 163)\n- `ListRuns()` - Returns all runs sorted by state (running first) and start time descending (line 193)\n- `ListRunsByProject()` - Returns runs filtered by project_dir with same sorting (line 224)\n- `ListProjects()` - Returns distinct project directories (line 243)\n- `ListChildRuns()` - Returns child runs of parent (line 262)\n- Database schema includes `container_kept` INTEGER field to track if container was retained\n\n**Runs List Page Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 254-300):\n- Filters by optional project query parameter\n- Counts retained containers per project\n- Returns runs with project metadata\n\n### 4. CONTAINER RUNTIME INTERFACE\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` lines 24-33):\n```go\nStart(ctx, cfg) (containerID string, error)\nStop(ctx, containerID string) error\nAttachOutput(ctx, containerID string) (ReadCloser, error)\nWait(ctx, containerID string) (exitCode int, error)\nCopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath string) error\nLogs(ctx, containerID string) (string, error)\nRemove(ctx, containerID string) error         // <- DELETE IMPLEMENTATION\nInspect(ctx, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)  // <- CHECK STATUS\n```\n\n**Docker Adapter** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`):\n- `Stop()` (line 154) - Calls `docker stop`\n- `Remove()` (line 219) - Calls `docker rm`\n- `Inspect()` (line 229) - Calls `docker inspect` with format template to get Running/ExitCode/FinishedAt\n\n**Local Adapter** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go`):\n- `Remove()` (line 145) - No-op (local processes don't need cleanup)\n- `Inspect()` (line 149) - Returns Running=false\n\n### 5. DOMAIN TYPES FOR RUN STATUS\n\n**Run States** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` lines 8-16):\n```go\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**Run Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` lines 31-47):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID            string\n    WorkflowName  string\n    State         RunState\n    ActiveSteps   []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt     time.Time\n    CompletedAt   time.Time\n    ProjectDir    string\n    ErrorMessage  string\n    ContainerID   string\n    BaseSHA       string\n    ContainerKept bool    // <-- Tracks retained containers\n    Title         string\n    IsHost        bool\n    ParentRunID   string\n}\n```\n\n### 6. WEB UI DELETION INTERFACE\n\n**Run Detail Page** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`):\n- Shows container status with badges (running, stopped, available, removed)\n- \"Delete Container\" button appears when:\n  - Run state is \"succeeded\", \"failed\", or \"cancelled\" (lines 27-29, 31-32)\n  - Container is in stopped or available state\n- Button calls `deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')` JavaScript function\n\n**JavaScript Delete Handler** (lines 308-326):\n```javascript\nwindow.deleteContainer = function(runID) {\n    fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })\n        .then(response.json())\n        .then(data => {\n            if (ok) {\n                statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>'\n            }\n        })\n}\n```\n\n**Project Detail Page** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`):\n- Shows container count button if any containers retained (line 10)\n- Button text: \"Delete N container(s)\"\n- Calls `deleteAllContainers()` JavaScript function\n\n**JavaScript Bulk Delete Handler** (lines 445-460):\n```javascript\nwindow.deleteAllContainers = function() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/' + projectLabel + '/containers', { method: 'DELETE' })\n        .then(r.json())\n        .then(data => {\n            btn.textContent = 'Deleted ' + data.deleted + ' containers'\n        })\n}\n```\n\n### 7. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture**:\n- Domain types in `/workspace/internal/domain/` are independent of infrastructure\n- Ports (interfaces) in `/workspace/internal/ports/` define contracts\n- Adapters in `/workspace/internal/adapters/` implement concrete backends:\n  - Docker adapter for container management\n  - Local adapter for local process execution\n  - SQLite adapter for persistence\n  - gRPC adapter for IPC\n  - Web adapter for HTTP/HTML UI\n\n**Handler Pattern**:\n- Handler accepts multiple optional dependencies via `HandlerOption` functions\n- Supports both HTML rendering and JSON API endpoints\n- Uses embedded templates and static files\n\n**Data Flow**:\n1. Web UI calls fetch() → HTTP route\n2. Handler retrieves data from store (RunStore interface)\n3. Handler calls container runtime (ContainerRuntime interface)\n4. Results persisted back to store\n5. Response sent as JSON or HTML\n\n### 8. KEY FILE LOCATIONS\n\n**Core Files**:\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run and RunState types\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - ContainerRuntime interface\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - HTTP handlers (1600+ lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` - Docker adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite persistence\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI commands (delete at line 79-80)\n\n**Web UI**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run details + delete button\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project page + bulk delete\n\n**Documentation**:\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` - Project page features\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - User-facing documentation\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - System architecture\n\n---\n\nThis covers all the major aspects: web UI structure with complete template and handler mappings, container deletion flow through both CLI and HTTP APIs, run/container management via the store, container lifecycle via the runtime interface, and domain types that define run states and container tracking."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa8f0dce72ad694b5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76484\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 165803</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e13d6e3-30e6-4db9-bdca-65dcaa963e36","uuid":"a814b3a2-ce93-4ff5-9014-69dc63529f01","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The web UI structure - find all HTML templates, handlers, and routes related to the \"Runs list page\"\n2. How container deletion currently works (the `cloche delete` command, and any existing delete/cleanup functionality in the web UI or API)\n3. The run store interface and how runs are listed/managed\n4. The container runtime interface and how containers are removed\n5. Any existing gRPC service definitions for delete/cleanup operations\n6. The domain types for Run status (completed, failed, etc.)\n\nSearch for: web UI templates, HTTP handlers, gRPC proto files, delete/cleanup related code, run statuses, container cleanup logic. Be very thorough - look at