ontainer count button if any containers retained (line 10)\n- Button text: \"Delete N container(s)\"\n- Calls `deleteAllContainers()` JavaScript function\n\n**JavaScript Bulk Delete Handler** (lines 445-460):\n```javascript\nwindow.deleteAllContainers = function() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/' + projectLabel + '/containers', { method: 'DELETE' })\n        .then(r.json())\n        .then(data => {\n            btn.textContent = 'Deleted ' + data.deleted + ' containers'\n        })\n}\n```\n\n### 7. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture**:\n- Domain types in `/workspace/internal/domain/` are independent of infrastructure\n- Ports (interfaces) in `/workspace/internal/ports/` define contracts\n- Adapters in `/workspace/internal/adapters/` implement concrete backends:\n  - Docker adapter for container management\n  - Local adapter for local process execution\n  - SQLite adapter for persistence\n  - gRPC adapter for IPC\n  - Web adapter for HTTP/HTML UI\n\n**Handler Pattern**:\n- Handler accepts multiple optional dependencies via `HandlerOption` functions\n- Supports both HTML rendering and JSON API endpoints\n- Uses embedded templates and static files\n\n**Data Flow**:\n1. Web UI calls fetch() → HTTP route\n2. Handler retrieves data from store (RunStore interface)\n3. Handler calls container runtime (ContainerRuntime interface)\n4. Results persisted back to store\n5. Response sent as JSON or HTML\n\n### 8. KEY FILE LOCATIONS\n\n**Core Files**:\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run and RunState types\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - ContainerRuntime interface\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - HTTP handlers (1600+ lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` - Docker adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite persistence\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI commands (delete at line 79-80)\n\n**Web UI**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run details + delete button\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project page + bulk delete\n\n**Documentation**:\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` - Project page features\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - User-facing documentation\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - System architecture\n\n---\n\nThis covers all the major aspects: web UI structure with complete template and handler mappings, container deletion flow through both CLI and HTTP APIs, run/container management via the store, container lifecycle via the runtime interface, and domain types that define run states and container tracking."}],"totalDurationMs":165803,"totalTokens":76484,"totalToolUseCount":47,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1994,"cache_read_input_tokens":71526,"output_tokens":2963,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1994},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
