{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":500168,"duration_api_ms":458668,"num_turns":32,"result":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**API endpoint** (`handler.go`):\n- `DELETE /api/containers` — new `handleAPIDeleteAllContainers` handler that iterates all runs across all projects, skips running containers and non-retained ones, removes stopped containers, clears the `ContainerKept` flag, and returns `{\"deleted\": N}`.\n\n**UI** (`runs.html`):\n- Added a \"Clean up N old containers\" button next to the project filter dropdown on the Runs list page. The button appears only when there are retained containers (`TotalContainerCount > 0`). Clicking it calls the new API endpoint, then updates the button text to show how many were cleaned up.\n\n**Template data** (`handleRunsList`):\n- Added `TotalContainerCount` to the template data by summing per-project container counts.\n\n**Tests** (`handler_test.go`):\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_Success` — verifies bulk deletion across multiple projects\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_SkipsRunning` — verifies running containers are not removed\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_SkipsNonKept` — verifies non-retained containers are ignored\n- `TestAPIDeleteAllContainers_NoManager` — verifies 400 when no container manager\n- `TestRunsList_CleanupButton` — verifies button appears with correct count\n- `TestRunsList_NoCleanupButtonWhenNoContainers` — verifies button is hidden when no retained containers\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8e13d6e3-30e6-4db9-bdca-65dcaa963e36","total_cost_usd":1.2687183000000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":30,"cache_creation_input_tokens":43009,"cache_read_input_tokens":973494,"output_tokens":8547,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":43009,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"model